⚔️ Deployment vs StatefulSet vs DaemonSet
🔹 1. Deployment (Stateless apps)

👉 Sabse common use hota hai

Concept:

Pods interchangeable hote hain (koi identity nahi)
Koi bhi pod delete ho jaye → naya pod aa jayega (same jaisa)

Use case:

Web apps (React, Node.js, APIs)
Microservices

Example:

myapp-abc123
myapp-def456

(random names, no identity)

Key points:

No fixed identity ❌
No persistent storage by default ❌
Fast scaling ✅
Rolling updates easy ✅
🔹 2. StatefulSet (Stateful apps)

👉 Jab data important ho

Concept:

Har pod ka fixed naam + identity
Har pod ka apna storage

Example:

mysql-0
mysql-1
mysql-2

Key points:

Stable identity ✅
Persistent storage ✅
Ordered start/stop ✅
Scaling controlled (slow but safe)

Use case:

MySQL, MongoDB, Kafka, Redis
🔹 3. DaemonSet (Node-level pods)

👉 Har node pe ek pod chalana ho

Concept:

Cluster ke har node pe ek pod automatically deploy hota hai

Example:

Agar 5 nodes hain → 5 pods automatically

Key points:

One pod per node ✅
New node add → pod auto deploy ✅
Node delete → pod remove ✅

Use case:

Monitoring agents (Prometheus Node Exporter)
Logging (Fluentd)
Security agents
🧠 Simple Analogy (yaad rehne wala)
Deployment → "Mujhe bas app chalani hai, koi bhi instance chalega"
StatefulSet → "Mujhe har instance ka naam + data yaad rehna chahiye"
DaemonSet → "Mujhe har machine pe ek agent chahiye"
